variables.description: Collection of blood between the dura mater and cranial theca, caused by fractures that can injure the middle meningeal artery or one of its branches. It may be associated with intracranial hypertension and cause coma, usually after a lucid interval. If promptly operated the prognosis is favourable.
variables.label: Epidural Hematoma

variables.description: tSAH is blood distributed in the subarachnoid space. Its location can be very limited for example in the interpeduncular space or over the tentorium. Otherwise it can be found in the cortical sulcus or on the brain vault.
variables.label: Traumatic subarachnoid haemorrhage
